HB 1231 Original 2026 Regular Session Berault
Abstract: Provides relative to Medicaid coverage for pregnant women.
Proposed law requires the La. Dept. of Health (LDH) to provide Medicaid coverage for
continuous glucose monitoring devices for Medicaid-eligible pregnant women diagnosed
with gestational diabetes requiring treatment with insulin.
Proposed law requires LDH to promulgate and adopt all rules and regulations necessary to
provide Medicaid coverage for continuous glucose monitoring devices to eligible
individuals.
Proposed law requires LDH to provide dental coverage for Medicaid-eligible pregnant
women. Proposed law further provides that dental coverage is limited to emergency
procedures.
Proposed law requires LDH to adopt and promulgate rules and regulations necessary to
provide dental coverage to Medicaid-eligible pregnant women.
(Adds R.S. 46:977.51 and 977.52)
